# 10.1 Introduction

Building an AI application involves far more than writing prompts or connecting a language model.

A production-ready AI system must execute consistently across different environments while coordinating multiple external services, runtimes, and dependencies.

The Study Abroad Finder project evolved through several implementation stages.

Each stage validated one architectural component before progressing to the next.

This incremental approach proved invaluable because it isolated failures and allowed every subsystem to be verified independently.

Rather than attempting to deploy the complete application immediately, the project followed a structured engineering methodology:

1. Build locally.
2. Verify functionality.
3. Deploy incrementally.
4. Isolate failures.
5. Resolve environment-specific issues.
6. Standardize the runtime.
7. Redeploy.
8. Validate again.

