# 10.15 Root Cause Analysis

At this point,

all evidence pointed toward the Filesystem MCP.

Unlike every other MCP server,

Filesystem MCP executes using:

```
npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem
```

This introduces a dependency on:

- Node.js
- npm
- npx

The Render Python runtime did not provide the execution environment expected by this MCP server.

This explained:

- Session failures
- Hanging tool calls
- Worker timeouts

The issue was environmental rather than architectural.

---

# 10.16 Why Docker Was Considered

Several possible solutions were evaluated.

Option A

Remove Filesystem MCP.

Option B

Replace Filesystem MCP with native Python file writing.

Option C

Standardize the runtime using Docker.

The third option preserved the original architecture while ensuring every runtime dependency was available.

