# 10.20 Key Lessons

The deployment journey demonstrated several important engineering principles:

- Local success does not guarantee cloud success.
- Runtime dependencies are as important as application code.
- Isolating components simplifies debugging.
- Incremental validation is more effective than full-system debugging.
- Docker is valuable not because it changes the application, but because it standardizes the environment in which the application runs.

Ultimately, Docker was not a workaroundвЂ”it became the correct deployment architecture for an application that combines Python-based and Node.js-based MCP servers within a single AI system.